<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>📜 RB002 Week 4 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Branching Dialogue — if / elseif / else · <strong>Course:</strong> Story Quest · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week your NPC remembers the story. A <strong>boolean</strong> like <code>questAccepted</code> holds the quest state, and <code>if / else</code> picks <strong>one</strong> reply.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the script. Before you imagine running it, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">local questAccepted = false

if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Good luck, hero!&quot;)
else
    print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Does it print <code>Good luck, hero!</code>? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">local questAccepted = true

if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Good luck, hero!&quot;)
else
    print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Now the boolean is true. Does it print <code>Good luck, hero!</code>? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows clean code first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The NPC should say only <strong>one</strong> line each talk.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Good luck, hero!&quot;)
else
    print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
end
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Good luck, hero!&quot;)
end
print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? When does the buggy question print?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The second talk should be different from the first talk.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Did you find my cat yet?&quot;)
else
    print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
    questAccepted = true
end
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Did you find my cat yet?&quot;)
else
    print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Which line is missing?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The NPC should say one line when the quest is accepted, and a different line when it is not. One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">if questAccepted then
    print(&quot;Good luck, hero!&quot;)
________
    print(&quot;Will you help me?&quot;)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>else</code> · <code>end</code> · <code>print</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your own quest world. Give your NPC two replies with <code>if / else</code> so the reply changes after you accept the quest. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of the dialogue changing, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My NPC says … the first time I talk.</p>
<p>After I accept the quest, my NPC says …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you talk to your NPC two times. Talk like you are teaching a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>if</strong>, <strong>else</strong>, <strong>boolean</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Press E the first time and show the NPC's first reply.</li>
<li>Press E again and show that the reply changed.</li>
<li>Say in your own words why only <strong>one</strong> line prints each time.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
